  <body>
   <p>(Budget for 1880)</p>
   <p>Expenditures estimated:</p>
   <table>
    <row>
     <cell>For interest on bonded debt</cell>
     <cell>$3,400.00</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
     <cell>Salary of Minister</cell>
     <cell>1,500.00</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
     <cell>Organist and Choir</cell>
     <cell>600.00</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
     <cell>School Purposes</cell>
     <cell>1,200.00</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
     <cell>Salary of Reader</cell>
     <cell>300.00</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
     <cell>Salary of Sexton</cell>
     <cell>500.00</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
     <cell>Salary of Janitor</cell>
     <cell>250.00</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
     <cell>Taxes</cell>
     <cell>400.00</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
     <cell>Fuel, Gas, Water</cell>
     <cell>400.00</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
     <cell>Incidentals</cell>
     <cell>300.00</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
     <cell>Total</cell>
     <cell>$8,950.00</cell>
    </row>
   </table>
   <p>It being assumed that the income for the next fiscal year would amount in dues for 86 members - $3,440: rent for parsonage, $480, and rent for pews $1,500, it was resolved to recommend an assessment of 7% on valuation of pews sold to make up the deficiency.</p>
